00:00:15.929 --> 00:00:18.539
Welcome to Client Server
Communications, a course

00:00:18.539 --> 00:00:19.919
about the web.

00:00:19.920 --> 00:00:23.670
Technically, the web is only
a small part of the internet.

00:00:23.670 --> 00:00:25.530
However, it is the only
part of the internet

00:00:25.530 --> 00:00:27.960
that people use without
even realizing that what

00:00:27.960 --> 00:00:30.219
they're using is the web.

00:00:30.219 --> 00:00:33.089
The web is the platform
that you, the web developer,

00:00:33.090 --> 00:00:35.950
can use to publish your
ideas to the world.

00:00:35.950 --> 00:00:38.490
It is the common language
between your servers

00:00:38.490 --> 00:00:40.950
and your clients.

00:00:40.950 --> 00:00:44.250
Every time you open a browser,
every time you download an app,

00:00:44.250 --> 00:00:47.130
every time you receive a
message on WhatsApp or Facebook,

00:00:47.130 --> 00:00:48.740
you're using the web.

00:00:48.740 --> 00:00:50.789
More generically,
in that very moment,

00:00:50.789 --> 00:00:54.369
a client is communicating
with a server, and vice versa.

00:00:54.369 --> 00:00:56.219
But what does that
actually mean?

00:00:56.219 --> 00:00:58.679
What's happening when you
navigate to a web site?

00:00:58.679 --> 00:01:01.670
How did the phone know that
somebody sent me a message?

00:01:01.670 --> 00:01:04.420
What capabilities does the web
have, and more importantly,

00:01:04.420 --> 00:01:06.420
what are its limitations?

